Some quick notes on cartographic nomenclature for The Decimal Labyrinth. (Nerd-core warning.) ...

... The Numogram divides primarily into two complementary regions, at first approximation an 'inside' (5:4, 7:2, 8:1, with 54 + 72 + 81 = 207), and an 'outside' (6:3, 9:0, with 63 + 90 = 153). It's complete number, and therefore number of its names = 207 + 153 = 360. ...

... The deep numerical beauty of this is easily seen through Plexenomy:
207: ((0)(0))(0)(0), which is Prime-9 x 9
153: ((00))(0)(0), which is Prime-7 x9 ...

... This immediately suggests that the Ccru was in error to label the region of the 9:0 syzygy (Illu) 'The Plex' since this is on vivid qabbalistic evidence a true name for the outside entirely. 
The Plex = 153 (AQ). ...
... But also, as an unexpected gift from the Lemurs, it has seven letters (153/9 = P-7). ...

... Taken as a guide, therefore, it suggests a name for the 'inside' modeled on that delivered by that recent vehicle of The Lofty Powers, Mission Impossible: The Final Reckoning. 
The Entity = 207 (AQ). It has nine letters, because 207/9 = P-9. ...
... Of course, innumerable alternative true names will be found for these regions, but this sets the minimal standard of numerical consistency.
... The Plex + The Entity = Xenotic Cosmogony.
